data.name: label1.Text
data.value:
Merge Skip Scenes: This will convert time to seconds and add the skip action and merge with another EDL file ( like the one above with only MUTE info ) in chronological order. So don't worry about your MUTE's or Skip scene info being perfect.
If you manually create a Skip Scene file, you can merge it with a Mute EDL file.
Format must be:
00:00:00.00 00:00:00.00 ^ START space STOP
The program will add the Skip Scene option "0"

data.name: label7.Text
data.value:
Add or subtract time from your EDL list.
Because sometimes the sync will be off for various reasons, mainly processor or audio card differences, you will need to modify the time by a second or two at the beginning or end.
You may use any integer or decimal up to six places. Subtract by putting a dash at the beginning of the number, like negative symbol.

data.name: ScanLbl.Text
data.value:
Scan a subtitle file (.srt) and automatically create a filter that takes out all bad language. You can use your own bad word file, or add, or subtract from the existing one.
Location: C:\Program Files (x86)\EDLMaker\bad_word_list.txt
